<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7727] Flush the regions corresponding to .META. more often</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7727</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We should flush the regions corresponding to .META. table more often. This will help reduce the log splitting time even more for the .META. region thereby improving the recovery time. Now that there is a separate hlog for meta (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7213&quot; title=&quot;Have HLog files for .META. and -ROOT- edits only&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7213&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7213&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), we can do this special case handling efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
