                            <comment id="13567385" author="anoopsamjohn" created="Thu, 31 Jan 2013 05:56:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the idea DD.&lt;br/&gt;
I think I came across some other existing issues which speaks abt this.  Or may be some I have seen in some mails. &lt;br/&gt;
So we will keep some thing like time bound flushes for Meta?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13568413" author="devaraj" created="Fri, 1 Feb 2013 02:49:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=anoopsamjohn&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;anoopsamjohn&quot;&gt;Anoop Sam John&lt;/a&gt;, yes, time bound seems reasonable to me. Will upload a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13569386" author="enis" created="Sat, 2 Feb 2013 02:15:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was trying to split my META table, and realized that most of the time, it is not flushed at all since it is lightly loaded. We should also do this for ROOT, just after we put some data, schedule a flush. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13569833" author="devaraj" created="Sun, 3 Feb 2013 18:02:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thinking about it, seems like we could merge this with the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5930&quot; title=&quot;Limits the amount of time an edit can live in the memstore.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5930&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5930&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch (with slightly special handling for meta). No need to do this differently..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
